Overview

This project was completed as part of the Alfido Tech Data Analyst Internship Task 3. The goal was to analyze web traffic behavior on Alfido Tech's music smart-link pages, identify top-performing content, and uncover opportunities to improve conversion rates. Dataset

Source: Kaggle — Website Traffic Dataset Raw Records: 226,278 | Cleaned Records: 122,567 Period: August 19–25, 2021 across 212 countries Event Types: Pageviews (73,360), Clicks (32,499), Previews (16,708) Features: event, date, country, city, artist, album, track, isrc, linkid

Analysis Performed

Daily event volume and traffic decay trends over 7 days Unique user retention and session-level engagement Top 10 landing tracks and exit pages by pageviews and clicks User journey funnel — Pageviews → Previews → Clicks Geographic traffic distribution and CTR by country Bounce rate analysis across markets Top artists by pageview traffic

Key Findings

Platform achieved a strong CTR of 44.3% and a bounce rate of 32.6% Only 22.8% of visitors triggered a preview — the biggest untapped conversion opportunity Jalebi Baby alone drove 6.2% of all pageviews, flagging a single-track dependency risk United States and India together accounted for ~40% of total traffic Nigeria led all markets in CTR at ~56%, followed by Pakistan and Saudi Arabia Traffic decayed ~15% from Thursday to Sunday, suggesting campaign-driven spikes

